   KOSOVO-NATO (Brussels, Belgium) _ A look at what NATO officials
now believe are the goals of the Yugoslav military: not only has
two months of bombing not broken the Serbs' will, there are
indications that a fundamental shift in strategy is under way. By
Michael Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL _ GENERAL (Moved in ``a'' category) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CEMETERY-THEFT (New York) _ Alastair Duncan has long been
regarded as one of the world's leading experts on Tiffany
stained-glass. He was an expert at Christie's auction house in New
York, has written books and articles on the subject, and has
consulted with the FBI in cases in which the government is
investigating crimes involving in stolen Tiffany stained glass
objects. But on Monday, federal authorities in Manhattan accused
Duncan of his own crimes, charging that he conspired others to buy
Tiffany stained-glass windows from grave robbers, and offering the
glass for sale overseas for hundreds of thousands of dollars.
</P>
<P>
   DETROIT-MURDER (Detroit) _ Grisly murder of a man in front of
his children at a gas station has brought protests and racial
tension with killer an Arab-American and dead father black. By
Robyn Meredith.
</P>
