<P>
   WINE-BROKERS (Undated) _ On a recent trip to the Napa Valley,
when the vineyards were ablaze with carpets of yellow mustard
flowers, my friend was hoping to purchase a case of wine she had
been unable to find in New York. She thought it would take no more
than a phone call. Instead, it turned into a 90-minute odyssey that
required her to drive to the vineyard, pay for the wine, have the
case loaded into her car and then transport it to a shipping
service suggested by the winery. Welcome to the wacky world of the
50 different sets of state regulations governing interstate
shipment of wine. By Marian Burros.
