<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COMMENTARY: Bubba-Wan Kenobi, with Litesaber
 &HT;    By John Kelso
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ There's been so much talk about this new ``Star
Wars'' prequel coming out that I figured I should jump into the
game. Here's what ``Star Wars'' would be like if it had been shot
in South Austin.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of fighting with lightsabers, the Jedi Knights would use
pool cues.
</P>
<P>
   The mantra would change from ``May the Force be with you'' to
``Let's you and me kick some space butt.''
</P>
<P>
   Darth Vader would admit he got the idea for the black clothing
from Johnny Cash.
</P>
<P>
   There would be several scenes in which Darth Vader gets beer all
over his mask from trying to drink through the hole.
</P>
<P>
   And he wouldn't be called Darth Vader. He would be called Garth
Vader.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of Alec Guinness, Obi-Wan Kenobi would be played by Burt
Reynolds.
</P>
<P>
   Every so often, Yoda would say, ``I know what. Let's barbecue
something.''
</P>
<P>
   Every so often, somebody would tell Yoda, ``Hey, rubber face,
why don't you just shut up.''
</P>
<P>
   Those airborne Harleys the Ewoks stole and rode around on
through the trees would have Miller Lite, Pennzoil and Red Man
decals on them.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of ``a long, long time ago in a galaxy far, far away''
it would read, ``somewheres back in there down toward Kyle.''
</P>
<P>
   Instead of Luke Skywalker, his name would have been Duke
Skywalker.
</P>
<P>
   Somebody would get a welding torch out of the truck and turn
R2-D2 into a keg.
</P>
<P>
   In the bar scene, a couple of the characters would use the Force
to cheat at shuffleboard, run up a large tab or get somebody else
to put money in the jukebox.
</P>
<P>
   There would be at least one scene where Stone Cold Steve Austin
hits Darth Vader over the head with a folding chair.
</P>
<P>
   Jabba the Hutt, the big, fat bad guy, would have been a used car
salesman called Jabba the Regular at Hut's. In the plot line, it
would be explained that he turned himself into a load from eating
too many double-meat cheeseburgers.
</P>
<P>
   Somebody would get a welding torch out of the truck and turn
C-3PO into a still.
</P>
<P>
   In the bar scene, a couple of the characters would have used the
Force to get the bartender to buy everybody a round, keep the place
open past closing time and get Queen Amidala from the prequel to
enter the wet T-shirt contest.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of almost falling in love, Luke Skywalker and his sister
Princess Leia would have gotten hitched, moved out to a
manufactured home off Nuckols Crossing Road and raised three
children named Li'l Bit, Scooter and String Bean. And the Austin
Independent School District wouldn't be able to find them on their
computers.
</P>
<P>
   Forget Princess Leia. The lead female interest would have been
Miss Bud Light.
</P>
<P>
   Chewbacca would have been called Manchaca, and of course his
name would have been pronounced Manchak.
</P>
<P>
   The wisecracking and flirtatious Han Solo would have been known
by all the gals as ``Hands'' Solo.
</P>
<P>
   Han Solo would have a ``Stop Honking, I'm Reloading'' bumper
sticker on the fender of his Millennium Falcon and a pair of fuzzy
dice hanging from the rear view mirror.
</P>
<P>
   There would be at least one scene with Han Solo on a creeper
under the Millennium Falcon changing out the oil.
</P>
<P>
   John Kelso writes for the Austin American-Statesman.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
