   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   MIDLIFE-JOURNEY _ ALLIANCE, Neb. _ As I drove to see
``Carhenge'' in Alliance, Neb., I kept saying to myself: ``There
has to be more to this than I've been told.'' A colleague told me
what I'd see: ``It's unbelievable. You go into this field off town
and this farmer's got a bunch of cars set up exactly like those
mysterious stone formations at Stonehenge in England.'' Carhenge?
Druid farmers in Nebraska? ``Trust me, you've got to see this.''
(Wiggins, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (l, a) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MANIC-MOMS _ The end of May and early June may be the busiest
weeks of a parent's year, except for Christmas. There are school
parties to organize, Brownie troop year-end camping trips to plan,
teacher gifts to buy and summmer daycare to line up, as well as the
wrapup of spring sports and the start of summer ones. Add in
vacations and juggling work schedules around your kids' needs, and
you've got the makings of parental stress. (Lee, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH ILLUSTRATION. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DOUBLE-DUTCH-JUMPROPE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Smack-dab in
this month's issue of ``Teen People'' is a fashion spread starring
Stan's Pepper Steppers, the reigning world champs of double-dutch
rope jumping. Bring down the old clothesline from grandma's attic.
This sport is cool. Double-dutch jumping, first popular in New York
City, involves two ropes twirling in opposite directions and one or
two jumpers doing tricks _ flips, rolls, push-ups, all without
stopping. (Anna, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FASHION-SPANDEX _ WACO, Texas _ S-T-R-E-T-C-H out and relax _
it's going to be a fluid-fit, wrinkle-free, comfy-as-can-be summer.
Stretchy spandex and Lycra fibers are showing up in trace amounts
in everything from clingy dresses to plus-size shirts and from
trousers to tailored jackets. (Mays, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
