<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   STARWARS-FANS _ ATLANTA _ Moviegoers donned their favorite
``Star Wars'' costumes _ from heroic Obi-Wan Kenobi to the evil,
black-hooded Emperor _ as the latest George Lucas sci-fi epic
opened on nearly 60 movie screens across metro Atlanta. Many
moviegoers gave the film a big thumbs up, but some found their
enthusiasm dimish as the 130-minute film plodded along. ``I camped
out seven hours for tickets,'' 26-year-old Paul Herris said after
watching the film Wednesday in DeKalb County. ``I wish I hadn't.''
Includes reports from across metro Atlanta, national info and local
Wookie Hooky participants from work and school. (Longino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   STARWARS-REACTIONS _ Audience reactions. (Larsen, Dayton Daily
News)
</P>
<P>
   STARWARS-NEWS _ Live news coverage of the lines, box office,
etc. (Stuever, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-ER _ Review of ER finale. (Kloer, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-FRASIER _ Review of Frasier finale one hour. (Kloer,
