<P>
   POSNANSKI: Sports columnist Joe Posnanski departs from his usual
interests to write about his opening-night screening of ``The
Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   BUST (with POSNANSKI). Star Wars fans don't care what the
critics say. The juggernaut has begun. Calvin Wilson.
</P>
<P>
   SIOUX: Tribal members occupy an island in the Missouri River in
South Dakota as they dispute land the Corps of Engineers is
returnign to the state. Scott Canon.
</P>
<P>
   WASTE _ Citizens Against Government Waste releases its annual
rankings of how our senators and representatives guarded the public
treasury last year. Sen. John Ashcroft scored 100. 12 inches. Kevin
Murphy.
</P>
<P>
   DATE: Area police are hearing more reports from young women that
go like this: A man in bar comes up to them and hands them a drink.
Not long afterward the women pass out. Then the women are raped.
Kansas City police says they're taking a minimum of two such
reports each week compared with none a year ago. Police say cases
of date rape drugs are difficult to prove because alcohol is
involved and often the women don't remember much. Rape crisis
centers report a similar increase. Christine Vendel. 20. Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   COLD: A cure for the common cold? Alan Bavley.
</P>
<P>
   STAFFORD (business) _ You've heard of permafrost. Have you heard
of permatemps? Microsoft has...and maybe wishes it hadn't. A
federal appellate court rules Microsoft should give thousands of
its long-time temp workers the same stock options as its employees.
Watch for the workplace fallout. At Work column by Diane Stafford.
</P>
