<P>
   AID-KOSOVO (Washington) _ Sen. Mitch McConnell, R-Ky., chairman
of the Senate subcommittee dispensing foreign aid, says post-war
reconstruction of Kosovo will cost $3 billion. Europe should pay 75
percent of that, he says, adding that the United States now has
long-term obligations to nations such as Albania and Macedonia
affected by the strife in the region. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   HILLARY-CLINTON-CAMPAIGN (Washington) _ Sen. Mitch McConnell,
R-Ky., who heads the National Republican Senatorial Campaign, says
the GOP relishes the prospect of First Lady Hillary Clinton running
for the Senate from New York. He questions the propriety of her
many trips to New York on Air Force jets, with Secret Service
agents and an entourage of aides _ all at taxpayers' expense. By
DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-POLITICS (Washington) _ Vicente Fox Quesada, Mexico's
leading opposition candidate for president, tells American
political experts here that his country will never crack down on
drug lords or fix its economy with the ruling party in power. By
MARK HELM.
