accepting Olivetti's $65 billion hostile takeover offer for the
company, potentially wrecking its proposed merger with Deutsche
Telekom. Telecom Italia's chairman schedules a late afternoon
conference call with big shareholders in an apparent attempt to
dissuade them. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
