<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:COVER:STAR-WARS-art-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COVER: ``STAR WARS: EPISODE 1 _ THE PHANTOM MENACE'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of actors Liam Neeson (left, with a
doorway behind him) and Ewan McGregor (right, with a stone wall
behind him), dueling with actor Ray Park (center) in a scene from
the movie ``Star Wars: The Phantom Menace.'' (CREDIT: Photo by
Keith Hamshere. Copyright 1999 Lucasfilm Ltd.) 
 By JESSAMY BROWN, with staff and wire service reports 
<TEXT>
<P>
   (Editor's note: Jessamy Brown, was age 7 when ``Star Wars'' came
out.)
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QC;
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars'' invasion begins this week (May 19).
</P>
<P>
   In our very own galaxy, a cinematic event will have occurred
that some folks have been waiting for all their lives. And even if
YOU haven't been, you won't be able to avoid it.
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace,'' a prequel to the
original trilogy, might be the most highly anticipated movie of all
time. Consider this:
</P>
<P>
   Moviegoers recently paid full price to get into theaters showing
``Phantom'' trailers _ preview clips shown before feature films _
and many left without seeing whatever movie was playing.
</P>
<P>
   Toys R Us stores around the country opened their doors at 12:01
a.m. May 3 for an all-night ``Phantom'' merchandise marathon.
</P>
<P>
   Fans began buying tickets weeks ahead of this week's opening.
</P>
<P>
   An estimated 2 million adults will take time off work to see the
flick.
</P>
<P>
   Kasey Nutter, 11, is so pumped about ``Phantom'' that her family
bought tickets early.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's just really exciting because I can kind of see the future
being like that. I think it would be cool if we could go in
different galaxies and meet aliens,'' said Kasey, a sixth-grader.
</P>
<P>
   Plot details for the new movie have been kept under wraps, but
it is known that it involves the introduction of a young Obi-Wan
Kenobi to Anakin Skywalker (who at some point becomes a Jedi
knight, turns to evil and becomes Darth Vader. Oh, and he is the
father of twins, Luke and Leia).
</P>
<P>
   The science-fiction epic started with ``Star Wars: Episode IV _
A New Hope,'' which opened on May 25, 1977. With $461 million in
ticket sales, it's second only to ``Titanic,'' which made $600
million. ``Phantom'' is expected to bring in $1.2 billion or more.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Empire Strikes Back'' opened in 1980 and ``Return of the
Jedi'' followed in 1983.
</P>
<P>
   The Star Wars tale is being told backward; the setting of
``Phantom'' and the upcoming prequels is ``before'' the trilogy. A
second prequel is scheduled to hit theaters in 2002. The third
installment is due out in 2005.
</P>
<P>
   Intergalactic Facts:
</P>
<P>
   Title: ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   Stars: Ewan McGregor plays young Obi-Wan Kenobi (a role made
famous in the original by Sir Alec Guinness). Samuel L. Jackson and
Liam Neeson play Jedi knights. Natalie Portman plays Queen Amidala,
the future mother of Luke Skywalker and Princess Leia. Jake Lloyd
plays Anakin Skywalker, the future Darth Vader.
</P>
<P>
   Rating: PG.
</P>
<P>
   Budget: Prequel: $110 million. Original: about $10 million.
</P>
<P>
   Cost of a Han Solo action figure in 1978: less than $15.
</P>
<P>
   Cost of the same action figure in mint condition in 1999: $550.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
