<SLUG> BC-KIDS:FACES-STAR-WARS:JAKE-LLOYD-art-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FACES: JAKE LLOYD, YOUNG ANAKIN SKYWALKER 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of young actor Jake Lloyd in a scene from
the movie ``Star Wars: The Phantom Menace.'' (CREDIT: Copyright
1999 Twentieth Century Fox.) 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Name: Jake Lloyd.
</P>
<P>
   Age: 10.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: Finishing fourth grade.
</P>
<P>
   Claim to fame: Plays a young Anakin Skywalker in ``Star Wars:
Episode I _ The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   Hobbies: Rides his bike, plays with friends, cares for his dog,
a Shih Tzu.
</P>
<P>
   Acting experience: Played Arnold Schwarzenegger's son in
``Jingle All the Way,'' plus parts in ``Unhook the Stars'' and the
television show ``ER.''
</P>
<P>
   Jake won the role of the future Darth Vader after a two-year
casting search. He plays an innocent slave boy who is strong with
the Force in Phantom Menace.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I got the part, I started yelling,'' he said. ``Then I
took a deep breath and thought, `Oh my gosh _ I got ``Star Wars!''
Then I yelled some more. Then I started crying,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Vader's always been my favorite ``Star Wars'' character,''
Jake said. ``Vader's really a good guy. He's the only one who could
destroy the emperor in the end'' (in ``Return of the Jedi''.)
</P>
<P>
   Jake loves video games, especially a new ``Star Wars Pod-Racer''
game he received before its May 20 release. He says the video game
version is more fun than it was shooting a pod race scene for the
movie, which he did while sitting still. A cheering crowd, roaring
engines, twisting race course and harrowing tunnels were inserted
later, using computer imagery.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've only played the pod-racing game for about five hours,''
Jake said Sunday. ``But I've beaten the first beginner stage.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
</P>
