<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-KIDS:STAR-WARS-QUOTES-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FAMOUS LINES FROM ``STAR WARS'' MOVIES 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Quotables:
</P>
<P>
   ``Hey, we don't serve their kind here.'' Mos Eisley, cantina
bartender.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sorry about the mess.'' Han Solo.
</P>
<P>
   ``Watch your mouth, kid, or you're going to find yourself
floating home.'' Han Solo.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's no moon. It's a space station!'' Obi-Wan Kenobi.
</P>
<P>
   ``Everything's under control. Situation normal. Had a slight
weapons malfunction.'' Han Solo.
</P>
<P>
   ``Aren't you a little short for a storm trooper?'' Princess
Leia.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is some rescue. ... Somebody has to save our skins. Into
the garbage chute, fly boy.'' Princess Leia.
</P>
<P>
   ``Will sombody get this big walking carpet outta my way?''
Princess Leia. (To which Han Solo remarks, ``No reward is worth
this.'').
</P>
<P>
   ``You came in THAT? You're braver than I thought.'' Princess
Leia.
</P>
<P>
   ``Run, Luke, run.'' Obi-Wan Kenobi.
</P>
<P>
   Test your knowlege of ``Star Wars'':
</P>
<P>
   1. What's so unusual about the sky on Luke Skywalker's home
planet of Tatooine?
</P>
<P>
   2. Where did Han Solo get his spaceship, the Millennium Falcon?
</P>
<P>
   3. Besides the three ``Star Wars'' feature films, there was one
television movie based on the series. What was it?
</P>
<P>
   4. Who played Darth Vader in all three movies?
</P>
<P>
   5. Where did Luke Skywalker first meet Han Solo?
</P>
<P>
   6. What does Yoda tell Luke he must do in order to become a true
Jedi knight?
</P>
<P>
   7. Only one actor in the original ``Star Wars'' films won an
Oscar, before or since. Who?
</P>
<P>
   8. Where on Earth would you go to find a place that looked like
Tatooine?
</P>
<P>
   Answers:
</P>
<P>
   1. Tatooine is in a system with two suns.
</P>
<P>
   2. Solo won the Falcon in a bet with Lando Calrissian, the
governor of Cloud City.
</P>
<P>
   3. ``The Ewok Adventure'' aired in 1984 on ABC, and focused on
the furry, tree-dwelling creatures.
</P>
<P>
   4. James Earl Jones supplied the voice; the man in the Sith
Lord's costume was actor David Prowse. Actor Sebastian Shaw was the
face of Darth Vader/Anakin Skywalker, but appeared only in
``Jedi.''
</P>
<P>
   5. Luke first meets Solo in a cantina on Tatooine.
</P>
<P>
   6. To become a Jedi knight, Luke must confront hi father, Darth
Vader.
</P>
<P>
   7. Alec ``Obi-Wan Kenobi'' Guinness won the Best Actor Oscar for
``The Bridge on the River Kwai'' in 1957.
</P>
<P>
   8. ``Star Wars'' _ and the new ``Phantom Menace'' _ were filmed
in part in the north African nation of Tunisia.
</P>
