<TEXT>
<P>
   High-Tech Diary
</P>
<P>
   Diary dilemma: You lose your key to the lock.
</P>
<P>
   No prob. The newest journals and diaries for girls are
electronic. Access is gained through creating, then using, a
``voice'' password. The Password Journal from Girl Tech, made by
Radica, is one such product that's bound to be a hot seller. Inside
is a secret key compartment, just in case you need to change your
password. Anything to keep that brother from spying on your private
thoughts.
</P>
<P>
   Pens With Punch
</P>
<P>
   Black ink is soooo boring. Pink, green, purple, silver and blue
are so much more fun for writing notes and doodling, says high
school student Megan Carroll. Pens take on every color of the
rainbow nowadays thanks to new plastic technology. Bic is drawing
young fans with its Shimmers line of six translucent colored pens,
priced at $2.99 a package.
</P>
<P>
   Bic Shimmers come in tropical shades of fuschia, lavender,
turquoise and lime.
</P>
<P>
   Odd Tooners
</P>
<P>
   Unless you've been sleeping in the Twilight Zone, you've seen
``Cat Dog,'' the popular Nickelodeon television series. Talk about
the ultimate odd couple. Dog enjoys rolling in the mud and eating
garbage while Cat wishes to pursue hobbies with dignity and
decorum. As a result, the fur often flies.
</P>
<P>
   From now through July, look for furry new CatDog toys from
Mattel, ranging from Stretch CatDog ($7.99) to Wacky Yakking
CatDog, an interactive plush toy that talks ($36).
</P>
<P>
   Razor Pizazz
</P>
<P>
   The glitter trend in makeup spills over to the bath with a new
line of sparkle razors from Gillette. The Women Sensor Dazzlers
come in three trendy, glittery hues __ ``Funky Fuschia,'' ``Go Girl
Green'' and ``Party on Purple.'' Each razor sells for $1.99 at
grocery stores and drugstores.
</P>
<P>
   Tips for beginners: 1. Get permission from a parent who can
teach you how to begin. 2. Soak area in warm water a few minutes to
soften hairs. 3. For smoother shaving and less dryness, use shaving
cream or gel. 4. Use a light touch and let the razor do the work
for you.
</P>
