<HEADLINE>
TRY OUR `STAR WARS' QUIZ AND WIN A VINTAGE POSTER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Answering ``Star Wars'' trivia isn't like dusting crops, boy.
Even if you've seen the trilogy multiple times, you may not have
what it takes to survive the Star-Telegram ``Star Wars'' trivia
challenge. Send entries to ``Star Wars'' trivia, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, c/o Catherine Gulley, Box 1870, Fort Worth, TX
76102; or e-mail to features\Nstar-telegram.com. Entries must be
postmarked by May 25. The grand-prize winner will be selected at
random from entries with all the correct answers. The winner will
receive an original ``Star Wars'' 1977 British poster, valued at
$200. And remember ... Do not try. Do. Or do not. There is no try
...
</P>
<P>
   1. What planet did Yoda live on?
</P>
<P>
   2. During the assault on the first Death Star, what was Luke's
call signal?
</P>
<P>
   3. Which intergalactic bounty hunter is credited with capturing
Han Solo?
</P>
<P>
   4. What type of droid is R2-D2?
</P>
<P>
   5. What race does Greedo belong to?
</P>
<P>
   6. What is the name of Darth Vader's command ship?
</P>
<P>
   7. What is the name of the Cantina Band?
</P>
<P>
   8. What class of ship is the Millennium Falcon?
</P>
<P>
   9. Name all the members of the Max Rebo band (including those
added in the special edition).
</P>
<P>
   10. Who commanded the second Death Star?
</P>
<P>
   11. What woman was recognized as the official ``leader'' of the
rebellion?
</P>
<P>
   12. What type of gas was mined on Cloud City?
</P>
<P>
   13. What was the name of Boba Fett's ship?
</P>
<P>
