<HEADLINE>
KEY RATES 
</HEADLINE>
  (js) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the daily key rates from The New York Times.
</P>
<P>
   ------------------Wednesday----Previous Day---Year Ago
</P>
<P>
   PRIME RATE ---------- 7.75 ------ 7.75 ------- 8.50
</P>
<P>
   DISCOUNT RATE ------- 4.50 ------ 4.50 ------- 5.00
</P>
<P>
   FEDERAL FUNDS(x) ---- 4.50 ------ 4.64 ------- 5.50
</P>
<P>
   3-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 4.47 ------ 4.51 ------- 5.05
</P>
<P>
   6-MO. TREAS. BILLS -- 4.57 ------ 4.63 ------- 5.13
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. INF(xx) 3.84 ------ 3.84 ------- 3.75
</P>
<P>
   10-YR. TREAS. NOTES - 5.59 ------ 5.65 ------- 5.60
</P>
<P>
   30-YR. TREAS. BONDS - 5.80 ------ 5.88 ------- 5.89
</P>
<P>
   TELEPHONE BONDS ----- 7.56 ------ 7.65 ------- 7.11
</P>
<P>
   MUNICIPAL BONDS(xxx) 5.36 ------ 5.38 ------- 5.24
</P>
<P>
   (x) Estimated daily average, Dow Jones Markets
</P>
<P>
   (xx) Realized dollar amount rises with inflation
</P>
