that large shareholders in the Italian telephone giant were leaning
toward a hostile $65 billion bid from Olivetti as the deadline for
acceptance approached. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   BARBOUR-LOBBY (Washington) _ As Republican national chairman,
Haley Barbour was a central strategist in his party's campaign to
cut the growth of Medicare. Now he has taken on a new assignment.
As a lobbyist for nursing homes, he pleads with Congress to undo
some of the damage done them by the law he helped write. By Robert
Pear.
</P>
<P>
   FIJI-DIET (Undated) _ Just a few years after the introduction of
television to a province of Fiji's main island, Viti Levu, eating
disorders _ once virtually unheard of there _ are on the rise among
girls, according to a study presented Wednesday at the American
Psychiatric Association meetings in Washington. By Erica Goode.
</P>
