BKN-LAKERNOTES (San Antonio) _ Notebook from the Lakers-Spurs
game. 
By Howard Beck. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERNOTES (Los Angeles) _ Notebook from the Dodgers-Astros
game. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-DEBATE (San Gabriel, Calif.) _ When the harbor seal population
began to diminish, the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service stepped in
and made it illegal to hunt, touch or hurt them. Noting that the
mountain lion's ranges are severely depleted, California voters
decided _ twice _ that no agency could kill one. Another state
measure bans the trapping of animals. And the Department of Fish
and Game was set to kill a population of beavers near Lake Skinner
in Riverside County that was threatening the endangered gnatcatcher
until a group of citizens stepped in. There are hundreds of federal
and state wildlife and conservation organizations supporting
various causes. But should these organizations dictate wildlife
policy? 
By Keith Lair/San Gabriel Valley Tribune. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-CYCLING-COLUMN (Arcadia, Calif.) _ A mountain biking tour of
the the Santa Anita Canyon area in the San Gabriel Mountains. 
By Mark Langton. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
OUT-PAULY-COLUMN (Castaic, Calif.) _ Column from the seventh annual
Bassing for Abused Kids trout derby at Castaic Lake. 
By Brett Pauly. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 

