<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, MAY 20
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-ISRAEL-BARAK-NYT (moved on Monday, May 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 17,
about Ehud Barak, Israel's Prime Minister-elect, misstated the
location of the Heffer Valley, the site of the kibbutz where Mr.
Barak was born. It is about 20 miles north of Tel Aviv near the
Mediterranean coast; it is not near the Lebanese border.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEXICO-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 18,
about the announcement by the Mexican Interior Minister, Francisco
Labastida Ochoa, that he will resign and run for President
misstated his age. He is 56.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CAMPAIGN-FINANCE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 18,
about the reinstatement of five criminal charges against Maria
Hsia, a Democratic fund-raiser, referred incorrectly to Vice
President Al Gore's role in the case. He was not identified as
legally responsible in any way in connection with the charges
against her.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-BALLANTINE-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 18)
</P>
<P>
   The obituary of Bill Ballantine sent by the New York Times News
Service on Tuesday, May 18, misstated his connection to the book
``Circus! From Rome to Ringling.'' He reviewed it for The Times in
1956; the author was Marian Murray.
</P>
