<P>
   Owners of homes in Carmel, Pebble Beach and Pacific Grove are
being asked to volunteer for a Raccoon Latrine Site Survey, says
the Carmel Pine Cone, in an item sent in by  &UR; Daryl Glen &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   Residents who would like to find out if raccoons have turned
their outdoors into outhouses should call the raccoon latrine site
study hotline at San Jose State University.
 &UR; William Murray  &LR; says he's hoping to be able to survey as many as
500 properties; the cost of this study is around $40,000.
</P>
